choices.text: You are given an array $a_{1}, a_{2}, \ldots, a_{n}$. You can remove at most one subsegment from it. The remaining elements should be pairwise distinct. In other words, at most one time you can choose two integers $l$ and $r$ ($1 \leq l \leq r \leq n$) and delete integers $a_l, a_{l+1}, \ldots, a_r$ from the array. Remaining elements should be pairwise distinct.
